						               													<description>From the rulesheet:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;The object of Lawyer, the Game is to be the Player with the most money at the end of the game.  You make money when you land on teal squares and you lose money when you land on fuchsia squares.  Suing and being sued are another way to make or lose money.  And at the end of the game, merchandise that you purchased along the way to The Good Life is figured into your final assets at a value 2 to 3 times greater than its original purchase price.&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A simple roll-and-move game with a spiraling track, and spaces where you can pick up event type cards and buy merchandise.  Has event spaces that allow you to &amp;quot;Sue your Neighbor&amp;quot;, at which time the player may choose to &amp;quot;sue&amp;quot; any other player, for whatever made-up reason they choose.  Lawsuits are settled by die rolls.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game also comes with several dime store type toys that represent merchandise.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game is subtitled &amp;quot;The hilarious game of negotiation and frivolous lawsuits&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
